Document: ResourceImporterImageFont
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterimagefont.rst
Summary: Provides import functionality for ImageFont resources.

Inherits: ResourceImporter < Resource

This class is used to import ImageFont resources into Godot. It handles the process of converting image-based font files into a format that Godot can use for rendering text. The importer allows for customization of import settings to fine-tune the appearance and behavior of the imported font.
---CHUNK---
Document: ResourceImporterImageFont
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterimagefont.rst
Summary: Imports a bitmap font where all glyphs have the same width and height.

ResourceImporterImageFont
Inherits: ResourceImporter < RefCounted < Object

Imports a bitmap font where all glyphs have the same width and height.
---CHUNK---
Document: ResourceImporterImageFont
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterimagefont.rst
Summary: Describes the ResourceImporterImageFont class, highlighting its suitability for fixed-width fonts and its differences from BMFont and DynamicFont importers.
This image-based workflow can be easier to use than ResourceImporterBMFont, but it requires all glyphs to have the same width and height, glyph advances and drawing offsets can be customized. This makes ResourceImporterImageFont most suited to fixed-width fonts. See also ResourceImporterDynamicFont.
---CHUNK---
Document: ResourceImporterImageFont
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterimagefont.rst
Summary: This document describes the ResourceImporterImageFont class, which is used for importing image-based fonts in Godot.

Inherits: ResourceImporter < ResourceImporter
Introduced in: 4.0

Overview

The ResourceImporterImageFont class is a built-in resource importer in Godot that handles the import of image-based fonts. These fonts are typically created from image files that contain the glyphs for a font.

Methods

Method: get_importer_name() → StringName
    Returns the unique name of the importer.

Method: get_visible_name() → StringName
    Returns the human-readable name of the importer.

Method: get_recognized_extensions() → PackedStringArray
    Returns a list of file extensions that this importer can handle.

Method: import(source_file: String, save_path: String, options: Dictionary, platform: String) → Error
    This method is called by Godot to import the resource. It takes the source file path, the destination save path, import options, and the target platform as arguments. It should return an Error code indicating success or failure.

Method: get_import_order() → int
    Returns the order in which this importer should be run relative to other importers.

Method: get_import_order_for_platform(platform: String) → int
    Returns the order in which this importer should be run for a specific platform.

Method: get_import_options(source_file: String, platform: String) → Array[Dictionary]
    Returns a list of import options that can be configured for this importer. Each option is a dictionary with keys like "name", "type", "default_value", and "hint".

Method: get_option_visibility(option_name: String, options: Dictionary, platform: String) → bool
    Returns whether a specific import option should be visible based on the current import options and platform.

Method: can_import(source_file: String, platform: String) → bool
    Returns whether this importer can handle the given source file for the specified platform.

