---CHUNK---
Document: ResourceImporterImageFont
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterimagefont.rst
Summary: Defines the properties used by the ImageFont resource importer.

Properties:
- ascent (int): The ascent of the font. Default: 0.
- character_margin (Rect2i): The margin around each character. Default: Rect2i(0, 0, 0, 0).
- character_ranges (PackedStringArray): The ranges of characters to include in the font. Default: PackedStringArray().
- columns (int): The number of columns in the font texture. Default: 1.
- compress (bool): Whether to compress the font texture. Default: true.
- descent (int): The descent of the font. Default: 0.
- fallbacks (Array): An array of fallback fonts. Default: [].
- image_margin (Rect2i): The margin around the entire font image. Default: Rect2i(0, 0, 0, 0).
- kerning_pairs (PackedStringArray): The kerning pairs for the font. Default: PackedStringArray().
- rows (int): The number of rows in the font texture. Default: 1.
- scaling_mode (int): The scaling mode for the font. Default: 2.
---CHUNK---
Document: ResourceImporterImageFont
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterimagefont.rst
Summary: Describes the properties and member variables for the ResourceImporterImageFont class in Godot Engine.

Property: ascent (int)
Default: 0
Description: Font ascent (number of pixels above the baseline). If set to 0, half of the character height is used.

Property: character_margin (Rect2i)
Default: Rect2i(0, 0, 0, 0)
Description: Margin applied around every imported glyph. If your font image contains guides (in the form of lines between glyphs) or if spacing between characters appears incorrect, try adjusting character_margin.

Property: character_ranges (PackedStringArray)
Default: PackedStringArray()
Description: The character ranges to import from the font image. This is an array that maps each position on the image (in tile coordinates, not pixels). The font atlas is traversed from left to right and top to bottom. Characters can be specified with decimal numbers (126), hexadecimal numbers (0x007e or U+007e), or between single quotes ('~'). Ranges can be specified with a hyphen between characters. For example, 0-127 represents the full ASCII range. It can also be written as 0x0000-0x007f (or U+0000-U+007f). As another example, ' '-'~' is equivalent to 32-126 and represents the range of printable (visible) ASCII characters. For any range, the character advance and offset can be customized by appending three space-separated integer values (additional advance, x offset, y offset) to the end. For example 'a'-'b' 4 5 2 sets the advance to char_width + 4 and offset to Vector2(5, 2) for both a and b characters.
Note: The overall number of characters must not exceed the number of columns multiplied by rows. Otherwise, the font will fail to import.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value.

Property: columns (int)
Default: 1
Description: Number of columns in the font image.

Property: compress (bool)
Default: true
Description: If true, uses lossless compression for the resulting font.

Property: descent (int)
Default: 0
Description: Font descent (number of pixels below the baseline). If set to 0, half of the character height is used.

Property: fallbacks (Array)
Default: []
Description: List of font fallbacks to use if a glyph isn't found in this bitmap font. Fonts at the beginning of the array are attempted first.

Property: image_margin (Rect2i)
Default: Rect2i(0, 0, 0, 0)
Description: Margin to cut on the sides of the entire image. This can be used to cut parts of the image that contain attribution information or similar.

Property: kerning_pairs (PackedStringArray)
Default: PackedStringArray()
Description: Kerning pairs for the font. Kerning pair adjust the spacing between two characters. Each string consist of three space separated values: "from" string, "to" string and integer offset. Each combination form the two string for a kerning pair, e.g, ab cd -3 will create kerning pairs ac, ad, bc, and bd with offset -3. \uXXXX escape sequences can be used to add Unicode characters.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value.

Property: rows (int)
Default: 1
Description: Number of rows in the font image.

Property: scaling_mode (int)
Default: 2
Description: Font scaling mode.